<headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 31 at 6:16PM EDT  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...Brief, but locally intense snow showers this evening...
Through 730 pm EDT...an area of snow showers will rapidly drop
east southeast across much of Berrien and Cass counties in
Michigan into eastern LaPorte, much of St Joseph and Elkhart
counties. the most intense snow showers will bring localized
visibility drops to a half mile or less. Snow may briefly
accumulate on elevated surfaces such as bridges and in grassy
areas with up to a quick half inch possible. Locally gusty winds
to 30 mph are also possible.
Use caution if encountering one of these snow showers when
travelling this evening.</description>
